<TITLE> China, India oppose 2050 emissions cut goal: France </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Toyako, Japan, July 09 (bndews24.com/Reuters) - China and India are not ready to agree to a goal set by the Group of Eight industrial nations to reduce emissions of greenhouse gases by 50 percent by 2050, a French presidential aide said on Wednesday. But the aide said the two fast-growing Asian economies, which together account for 25 percent of the emissions that scientists say are contributing to global warming, would be willing to take action later.
